        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "Mathematics likes to hide **big ideas** in *short symbols*. The most famous of all,\nEuler's identity $$e^{i\\pi} + 1 = 0$$, ties together five constants in a single breath —\nnote how $$e^{i\\pi}$$ sits *inside* this sentence. marklower also styles `inline code`,\n__bold__, and ~~struck-out~~ text.\n",
          "array": false,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": []
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "When a formula deserves a line of its own, give it a whole chunk — see the Gaussian\nintegral at [/[2]](/[2]), a standalone LaTeX block (that link is relative to\nthis document; the title, being the node's self-value, consumes no index).\n",
          "array": false,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": []
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\infty} e^{-x^2}\\,dx = \\sqrt{\\pi}\n",
          "array": false,
          "set": false,
